5177, "The Soter line of support cruisers are designed to accompany front-line capital ships during the early stages of pitched battles. Capable of firing devastating rounds of high velocity missiles from the safety of behind the front lines, a group of Soters in close formation (often referred to as a 'Soterball') can easily take down a corvette or tenderize a destroyer for strike groups to take down. her missile armament appears to be derived from Jovian observation of our Skotas class. It has replaced the old Fenris and Leviathan cruiser lines in Jovian service."

